description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced Ward Clerk to join the team on Ward 8 at the University Hospitals of North Midlands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward 8 sits within the Division of Specialised Surgery and is located at the County Hospital site in Stafford. Ward 8 Specialising in Bariatric Metabolic Surgery, Gynaecology Surgery, Breast Surgery and Day Surgery. Ward 8 provides care for Pre and Post-Operative Surgical adults over a 5 day Monday-Friday week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to provide effective clerical and administrative duties working alongside the Nursing and Medical team and wider MDT. You will be required to check, collect and input patient data on to the Trust’s IT systems such as Medway, File fast and I-Portal. The post holder will have excellent communication, organisational and leadership skills. You will be expected to work in a flexible manner to meet the needs of the service. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJulie WilliamsJob titleSenior SisterEmail addressjulie.williams2@uhnm.nhs.ukTelephone number01785 230066Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in joining our Team and require more information or wish to arrange an informal visit please contact -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Senior Sister Williams - 01785 230066&lt;/p&gt;
